00:25:51,366 --> 00:25:53,857
You're so beautiful.

244
00:25:54,569 --> 00:25:56,469
Prison agrees with me.

245
00:25:56,638 --> 00:25:58,538
There's no hypocrisy here.

246
00:25:58,707 --> 00:26:02,837
Kill or be killed,
and everybody knows it.

247
00:26:04,246 --> 00:26:06,077
Do they hurt you?

248
00:26:07,249 --> 00:26:09,479
Not as much as I hurt them.

249
00:26:12,454 --> 00:26:16,584
I won't be in here forever.
I promise you that.

250
00:26:16,758 --> 00:26:20,558
One day you'll look out your window
and I'll be there.

251
00:26:22,897 --> 00:26:25,764
Your hair smells like clover.

252
00:26:27,502 --> 00:26:33,964
I wanna remember you just like this,
in that sadly hopeful pink dress.

253
00:26:35,377 --> 00:26:39,143
-Starr picked it out.
-Of course she did.

254
00:26:42,817 --> 00:26:44,375
What's that?

255
00:26:46,187 --> 00:26:49,384
Nothing. It's just a cross.

256
00:26:49,557 --> 00:26:51,923
I know it's a cross.

257
00:26:54,362 --> 00:26:56,887
Why are you wearing it?

258
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:01,526
It's a present from Starr.

259
00:27:01,836 --> 00:27:03,861
She force you to go to church?

260
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:08,032
They're really nice people.
It's called the Assembly of God.

261
00:27:08,209 --> 00:27:13,909
To join you have to accept Christ as your
personal savior. And you're baptized.

262
00:27:14,082 --> 00:27:19,611
They call it being washed in the blood
of the Lamb. But really, it's just water.

263
00:27:21,189 --> 00:27:25,148
Have you accepted Christ
as your personal savior?

264
00:27:25,327 --> 00:27:30,162
-There's nothing wrong with Christians.
-Are you out of your mind?

265
00:27:31,666 --> 00:27:36,535
How did this happen? I raised you,
not Bible-thumping trailer trash.

266
00:27:36,705 --> 00:27:39,333
I raised you to think for yourself.

267
00:27:39,507 --> 00:27:41,771
No, you didn't.

268
00:27:45,347 --> 00:27:47,781
You raised me to think like you.

269
00:27:47,949 --> 00:27:53,910
Maybe thinking for yourself isn't so
great. Reverend Daniels says it's evil.

270
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:59,925
Evil? If thinking for yourself is evil,
then every artist is evil.

271
00:28:00,095 --> 00:28:05,533
Is that what you believe, now that
you're washed in the blood of the Lamb?

272
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:10,160
-Man's ability to reason is evil? Am I evil?
-No.

273
00:28:12,006 --> 00:28:13,871
No.

274
00:28:14,876 --> 00:28:18,778
But killing people who
don't want you is evil.

275
00:28:18,947 --> 00:28:20,915
We pray for your redemption.

276
00:28:21,082 --> 00:28:25,018
Fuck my redemption. I don't want it.
I regret nothing.

277
00:28:25,186 --> 00:28:30,988
Attention. Visiting hours are over.
Visitors, return to the holding area.

278
00:28:31,393 --> 00:28:34,988
It's good that you're trying
to identify evil, Astrid.

279
00:28:35,764 --> 00:28:37,823
But evil is tricky.

280
00:28:37,999 --> 00:28:42,959
Just when you think you know
what it is, it changes its form.

281
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:46,699
Learning its nature takes
a lifetime of study.

282
00:28:47,308 --> 00:28:51,938
I will not lose you.
Not to them.

283
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:55,745
Those people are the enemy, Astrid.

284
00:28:55,917 --> 00:28:58,852
-Visiting hours are over.
-Write to me.

285
00:28:59,020 --> 00:29:00,749
-Time's up.
-Write to me...

286
00:29:00,922 --> 00:29:03,618
-...at least once a week.
-I love you.

287
00:29:03,792 --> 00:29:08,991
I'm the only person you know
who can keep you honest.

288
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:11,689
-Okay?
-Okay.

289
00:29:14,302 --> 00:29:18,432
Don't forget who you are, Astrid.

290
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:23,034
You're my daughter
and you're perfect, remember?

291
00:29:55,543 --> 00:29:57,477
How far away is it?

292
00:29:57,645 --> 00:30:00,978
About a mile. Maybe two.

293
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:03,414
Shouldn't we pack up and go?

294
00:30:03,585 --> 00:30:07,521
No, not yet. The wind's still in our favor.

295
00:30:11,292 --> 00:30:13,817
My mother used to love fire season.

296
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:19,564
She made me decide what I'd take
if we had to go.

297
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:23,693
She said if I was brave,
I wouldn't take anything.

298
00:30:25,173 --> 00:30:27,368
Your mother sounds tough.

299
00:30:27,542 --> 00:30:28,770
Not like you.

300
00:30:30,778 --> 00:30:32,837
What am I like?

301
00:30:33,581 --> 00:30:36,982
You? You're a sweetheart.

302
00:30:44,993 --> 00:30:46,984
Astrid, honey?

303
00:30:47,762 --> 00:30:49,559
Astrid?

304
00:30:51,032 --> 00:30:53,159
You come on in here a minute?

305
00:31:00,608 --> 00:31:03,042
Well, sit down. I won't bite.

306
00:31:08,049 --> 00:31:13,681
You having fun here, aren't you? Making
yourself at home, getting comfortable?

307
00:31:16,157 --> 00:31:18,717
Little too comfortable, I'd say.

308
00:31:19,761 --> 00:31:24,755
I might not be a genius, but I get your
game. And it takes one to know one.

309
00:31:24,933 --> 00:31:27,834
-One what?
-Always hanging around...

310
00:31:28,002 --> 00:31:32,166
...handling his tools.
"What's this for, Ray? Can I help you?"

311
00:31:32,340 --> 00:31:34,774
We're not doing anything.

312
00:31:35,376 --> 00:31:37,640
I'm calling Children's Services.

313
00:31:37,812 --> 00:31:39,609
-It's all over.
-But...

314
00:31:39,781 --> 00:31:41,772
Don't "but" me.

315
00:31:43,017 --> 00:31:47,647
He is a man. And he sees what he sees,
and he does what he can.

316
00:31:47,822 --> 00:31:50,052
I've got a nice thing going here.

317
00:31:50,224 --> 00:31:52,249
Ray's the best man I ever had.

318
00:31:52,427 --> 00:31:56,124
And I've lived too long
and come too far to blow it now.

319
00:31:58,032 --> 00:32:00,466
I never had a father...

320
00:32:00,635 --> 00:32:02,296
Don't.

321
00:32:03,438 --> 00:32:08,102
I've got myself and my kids to worry
about. We hardly know each other.

322
00:32:08,276 --> 00:32:10,608
I don't owe you a thing.

323
00:32:12,981 --> 00:32:18,817
-Jesus would give me a chance.
-Well, I'm not Jesus. Not even close.

324
00:32:23,791 --> 00:32:26,225
He might be mad...

325
00:32:26,461 --> 00:32:30,397
...if he knew you sent me away
because you were jealous.

326
00:32:31,899 --> 00:32:35,699
You're trying to make him a prisoner.
He's gonna hate you.

327
00:32:38,339 --> 00:32:39,601
What do you know?

328
00:32:39,774 --> 00:32:43,266
I know that men don't like women
who try to own them.

329
00:32:44,045 --> 00:32:49,677
I like you. I like the kids. I would
never do anything to screw it up.

330
00:32:52,153 --> 00:32:55,247
You swear you're not
interested in him?

331
00:32:55,423 --> 00:32:57,550
I swear to God.

332
00:33:02,563 --> 00:33:06,795
-There. Did you see it?
-I'm not sure.

333
00:33:07,368 --> 00:33:09,893
-See anything yet?
-It's just starting.

334
00:33:10,071 --> 00:33:12,767
But we should be getting
40 an hour soon.

335
00:33:12,940 --> 00:33:16,899
The Quadrantid is the shortest
meteorite shower, but the densest.

336
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:19,239
Except for the Perseids.

337
00:33:28,723 --> 00:33:31,317
You and Starr, you having a beef?

338
00:33:33,995 --> 00:33:35,519
No.

339
00:33:36,631 --> 00:33:38,189
Why?

340
00:33:40,234 --> 00:33:42,725
Just something she said.

341
00:33:47,875 --> 00:33:50,469
I guess it's hard getting older...

342
00:33:51,379 --> 00:33:54,507
...pretty girl coming up in the house.

343
00:33:55,316 --> 00:33:59,582
Ray, honey? What are
you doing out here?

344
00:33:59,754 --> 00:34:02,746
Nothing, baby.
Just having a smoke.

345
00:34:10,898 --> 00:34:13,093
Looking at the stars.

346
00:34:21,075 --> 00:34:23,543
And this is $40,
not even $40 a month.

347
00:34:23,711 --> 00:34:27,078
-Forty dollars is $40.
-You waste $200 in one night.

348
00:34:27,248 --> 00:34:30,376
-You've been doing it weekly.
-I won last week.

349
00:34:30,551 --> 00:34:33,418
What else are you doing
with the money, Ray?

350
00:34:33,588 --> 00:34:36,853
-You can't even look at me.
-I'm looking right at you.

351
00:34:37,024 --> 00:34:40,619
You weren't. And you've got
your car out there.

352
00:34:40,795 --> 00:34:43,286
God knows what you spend on that.

353
00:34:43,464 --> 00:34:45,329
That comes out of my pocket.

354
00:34:45,666 --> 00:34:48,066
-Don't ruin this.
-Ruin what?

355
00:34:48,236 --> 00:34:50,136
You didn't come in till 3:00
in the morning.

356
00:34:50,304 --> 00:34:53,967
-I was with John.
-She's drinking again.

357
00:34:54,142 --> 00:34:56,667
And who else?
I saw you eyeing her.

358
00:35:14,428 --> 00:35:16,862
Thought you all were
going to a movie.

359
00:35:17,031 --> 00:35:19,124
I had a lot of homework.

360
00:35:20,968 --> 00:35:25,996
-How come you aren't playing poker?
-The game got cancelled.

361
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:33,003
-They coming home soon?
-Not too long.

362
00:35:35,850 --> 00:35:39,183
Well, there's plenty
of food if you want.

363
00:35:40,021 --> 00:35:41,852
Thanks.

364
00:36:22,129 --> 00:36:24,290
This isn't right.

365
00:37:14,916 --> 00:37:16,816
Is everyone gone?

366
00:37:20,554 --> 00:37:24,513
-It is my business! This is my house!
-It is not!

367
00:37:24,692 --> 00:37:28,287
-Get out of my room!
-You abide by the laws I put down!

368
00:37:28,462 --> 00:37:33,559
I am not gonna get out! I waited up for
you. I want to know who you were with!

369
00:37:33,734 --> 00:37:36,828
Don't give me your shit.
You stayed up to drink.

370
00:37:37,004 --> 00:37:40,770
-I stayed up to catch you, you whore!
-You should know.

371
00:37:43,044 --> 00:37:46,480
Try it again,
I'll take you out, bitch.

372
00:37:47,949 --> 00:37:52,648
Carolee! You walk out that door,
don't you bother coming back.

373
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:58,224
Why the hell would I want to? I've been
down this road with you before, Mom.

374
00:37:59,260 --> 00:38:02,752
Sorry, Davey.
I can't go through this again.

375
00:38:04,799 --> 00:38:06,528
Carolee.

376
00:38:17,278 --> 00:38:22,147
You used to like it before you started
doing that bitch. Admit it, bastard!

377
00:38:22,516 --> 00:38:24,541
-You're screwing her!
-You need to call your sponsor.

378
00:38:24,719 --> 00:38:27,654
-Screw my sponsor!
-Go back to bed.

379
00:38:27,822 --> 00:38:31,314
I should've gotten rid of her.
Know what I'm gonna do?

380
00:38:31,792 --> 00:38:34,158
I'm gonna go in there
and cash her check.

381
00:38:34,328 --> 00:38:39,163
Hey, Starr. Starr. Hey! Starr!
Give me that gun.

382
00:38:40,167 --> 00:38:42,965
-What the hell is wrong with you?
-Get off!

383
00:38:45,539 --> 00:38:48,269
Starr! Starr!

384
00:38:50,344 --> 00:38:53,438
Get off of me, goddamn it!
Get off of me!

385
00:38:53,614 --> 00:38:58,347
No, Ray! Goddamn it, Ray.
Get off of me!

386
00:39:14,635 --> 00:39:20,699
No, don't cry. We're not like that.
We're the Vikings, remember?

387
00:39:20,908 --> 00:39:25,777
Astrid? Can you talk to me? Astrid?

388
00:39:25,946 --> 00:39:31,475
Astrid? Can you talk to me? Astrid.
Talk to me. Can you talk to me?

389
00:39:31,652 --> 00:39:36,453
She's coming around. This boy saved
your life. If he hadn't called 911 ...

390
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:39,718
-...you'd be dead.
-Who did this to you, Astrid?

391
00:39:39,894 --> 00:39:42,556
-Who shot you?
-I don't know.

392
00:39:43,531 --> 00:39:45,499
Hey, watch your feet.

393
00:39:45,666 --> 00:39:47,395
-Okay, rug.
-Got it.

394
00:39:49,537 --> 00:39:55,339
-Where's Ray, Davey?
-He's gone. They're both gone.

395
00:39:57,011 --> 00:40:01,243
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry I ruined it.

396
00:40:01,415 --> 00:40:04,509
Doesn't matter.
Something would have.

397
00:40:04,819 --> 00:40:06,878
Bye, Astrid.

398
00:40:07,054 --> 00:40:08,112
Okay. One step.

399
00:40:08,289 --> 00:40:10,757
-Davey.
-We got you, Astrid.

400
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:13,593
Okay, step.

401
00:40:18,699 --> 00:40:20,428
We got her.

402
00:40:23,504 --> 00:40:26,803
It's okay. We got you.

403
00:41:02,510 --> 00:41:07,277
We'd prefer to find a permanent place,
but we have so many children right now.

404
00:41:07,448 --> 00:41:11,043
You need special attention,
which you'll get at McKinney Hall.

405
00:41:11,218 --> 00:41:13,914
They have all sorts
of activities for kids.

406
00:41:22,530 --> 00:41:26,261
You're dead, bitch!
You hear me? You're dead.

407
00:41:27,201 --> 00:41:31,331
Don't ever look at my boyfriend
again. You hear me?

408
00:41:31,505 --> 00:41:33,769
You look at my boyfriend,
you're dead!

409
00:42:48,048 --> 00:42:53,611
Next time you and your friends jump me,
I'll cut your throats when you're sleeping.

410
00:43:10,137 --> 00:43:15,165
-What do you want?
-I was looking at your picture.

411
00:43:16,744 --> 00:43:18,109
It's good.

412
00:43:20,347 --> 00:43:21,780
Who is it?

413
00:43:28,289 --> 00:43:32,385
-How come you chopped off your hair?
-None of your business.

414
00:43:36,163 --> 00:43:39,462
-You're still beautiful.
-Looks don't interest me.

415
00:43:40,501 --> 00:43:44,028
That's easy for you to say.
You've never been ugly.

416
00:44:09,930 --> 00:44:15,493
Look. It's the puta.
She's so ugly now.

417
00:44:53,607 --> 00:44:55,507
You're not ugly.

418
00:45:04,051 --> 00:45:08,317
You write as if you're surprised
to find me still beautiful even here.

419
00:45:08,489 --> 00:45:11,754
Our beauty is our power, our strength.

420
00:45:11,925 --> 00:45:15,793
We can't allow them
to change us, to lessen us.

421
00:45:15,963 --> 00:45:22,266
I will never grant them that
satisfaction and neither should you.

422
00:45:30,944 --> 00:45:34,402
So is this your first time in Mac?

423
00:45:35,883 --> 00:45:39,284
Figured. You're so unfriendly.

424
00:45:40,020 --> 00:45:44,821
-Life's easier without friends.
-Maybe. I like it here.

425
00:45:44,992 --> 00:45:50,658
It's better than being in a foster home.
It's the floor you can't fall below.

426
00:45:56,837 --> 00:45:59,829
-What's that?
-A letter.

427
00:46:00,007 --> 00:46:03,738
-From who?
-My mother.

428
00:46:04,778 --> 00:46:08,373
-And where is she?
-In prison. For murder.

429
00:46:09,583 --> 00:46:12,814
-And your father?
-Don't know the guy.

430
00:46:15,956 --> 00:46:17,821
How about you?

431
00:46:18,258 --> 00:46:19,850
They were junkies.

432
00:46:20,027 --> 00:46:23,554
She OD'd when I was 6.
He disappeared a couple years later.

433
00:46:23,730 --> 00:46:27,291
-I was born addicted to heroin.
-Really? What was that like?

434
00:46:27,468 --> 00:46:31,302
I don't know. I was out of rehab
by the time I was six months old.

435
00:46:34,675 --> 00:46:36,199
So...

436
00:46:38,612 --> 00:46:41,581
-What's the deal? Are you gay?
-What?

437
00:46:41,748 --> 00:46:47,846
I don't know. I get this feeling from you,
like you're not interested in guys.

438
00:46:49,823 --> 00:46:51,916
You're right. I'm not.

439
00:46:52,192 --> 00:46:56,891
You think that's funny? I'm sick of this.
I'm not gonna let you do this again.

440
00:46:57,064 --> 00:47:00,124
Why don't you shut up?
You're not even in this.

441
00:47:00,300 --> 00:47:02,632
-Cut it out.
-She does this shit.

442
00:47:02,870 --> 00:47:06,601
I'll beat your ass.
Wait until we get off the van.

443
00:47:06,773 --> 00:47:09,298
-Back off.
-I'm gonna push you farther.

444
00:47:13,580 --> 00:47:17,209
-What if they catch us?
-They'd put us in McKinney Hall.

445
00:47:17,384 --> 00:47:19,511
-Hurry.
-Come on.

446
00:47:20,254 --> 00:47:21,983
Come on, come on.

447
00:47:24,358 --> 00:47:26,417
The guy's a genius.

448
00:47:26,960 --> 00:47:31,226
I started out copying his stuff,
but no...

449
00:47:31,398 --> 00:47:33,559
I could never touch him.

450
00:47:35,269 --> 00:47:39,638
He's great. But you're better.

451
00:47:42,543 --> 00:47:44,374
You're insane.

452
00:47:48,148 --> 00:47:53,279
No, I'm not. I mean, he's a great
cartoonist, but you're an artist.

453
00:47:54,221 --> 00:47:56,712
What's the difference?

454
00:47:56,890 --> 00:48:01,486
Well, that's like asking
why a joke is funny.

455
00:48:01,662 --> 00:48:06,326
Either it's funny or it's not.
You're either an artist or you're not.

456
00:48:06,500 --> 00:48:08,127
You are.

457
00:48:32,292 --> 00:48:37,025
It's hard because they keep moving.
That's good.

458
00:48:38,198 --> 00:48:40,132
Don't look. I'm not done.

459
00:49:47,134 --> 00:49:50,729
-There's another one. Do you see it?
-Yeah.

460
00:49:58,679 --> 00:50:02,410
The Lyrids shower is visible
most of the night.

461
00:50:02,582 --> 00:50:05,176
The brightest star is Vega.

462
00:50:05,585 --> 00:50:09,715
But you can't look right at it
or you'll miss the fainter meteors.

463
00:50:09,890 --> 00:50:12,324
You can trace them back to Lyra.

464
00:50:14,728 --> 00:50:17,060
How do you know all that?

465
00:50:20,300 --> 00:50:22,564
A kid I used to know.

466
00:50:34,247 --> 00:50:37,808
I used to have a foster home
right over there.

467
00:50:43,557 --> 00:50:45,889
It's nice living on the beach.

468
00:50:52,899 --> 00:50:55,595
Do you ever think about your father?

469
00:50:58,638 --> 00:51:01,232
Not really. He was an asshole.

470
00:51:05,779 --> 00:51:08,543
I think about mine sometimes.

471
00:51:10,383 --> 00:51:12,749
That when I'm an artist...

472
00:51:12,919 --> 00:51:17,356
...he'll read about me in the papers
and he'll want to meet me.

473
00:51:25,899 --> 00:51:27,833
I'm not gay.

474
00:51:30,737 --> 00:51:32,170
I know that.

475
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:01,232
I'll show you the one
that he did of me.

476
00:52:08,542 --> 00:52:11,739
It's right here.

477
00:52:12,279 --> 00:52:15,146
They're not bad, for what they are.

478
00:52:16,316 --> 00:52:19,911
For what they are?
What are they?

479
00:52:20,620 --> 00:52:22,747
Cartoons.

480
00:52:23,290 --> 00:52:24,780
No, they're not.

481
00:52:24,958 --> 00:52:29,224
