485
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:46,237
Loneliness is the human condition.
No one is ever going to fill that space.

486
00:52:46,413 --> 00:52:50,941
The best you can do is know yourself.
Know what you want.

487
00:52:51,117 --> 00:52:54,177
And don't let the cattle
get in the way.

488
00:52:54,588 --> 00:52:58,854
You're not talking about me.
You're talking about yourself.

489
00:52:59,259 --> 00:53:03,457
Sometimes I get the feeling you
don't even want me to be happy.

490
00:53:04,764 --> 00:53:07,324
Why wouldn't I want you to be happy?

491
00:53:17,277 --> 00:53:21,236
-Where are they sending you?
-I don't know.

492
00:53:24,851 --> 00:53:26,375
Look.

493
00:53:30,323 --> 00:53:33,292
The comic book store
will hold letters for me.

494
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:36,918
Wherever they take you,
keep checking there.

495
00:54:38,758 --> 00:54:42,057
Why do we have to go
to Mexico to buy this stuff?

496
00:54:42,228 --> 00:54:44,662
It isn't FDA approved.

497
00:54:46,633 --> 00:54:50,535
-What's it called?
-DMSO.

498
00:54:51,771 --> 00:54:57,334
-What's it for?
-All sorts of things.

499
00:55:01,815 --> 00:55:07,947
You'll like these people. She's an actress
and he does something with television.

500
00:55:08,989 --> 00:55:14,052
-Do they have any kids?
-No. They're looking to adopt.

501
00:56:05,845 --> 00:56:08,439
She's had an incredibly hard time.

502
00:56:08,615 --> 00:56:12,847
She's very smart.
She's just missed a lot of school.

503
00:56:13,686 --> 00:56:17,349
-You don't have to decide immediately.
-Okay.

504
00:56:17,524 --> 00:56:19,992
Just talk to her.

505
00:56:20,160 --> 00:56:23,618
If you're uncomfortable
in any way, just let me know.

506
00:56:38,043 --> 00:56:40,034
There you are.

507
00:56:41,880 --> 00:56:48,080
I'm really sorry Mark couldn't be here
to meet you. He's filming in Nova Scotia.

508
00:56:48,920 --> 00:56:52,321
Well, this is it.
I left it plain on purpose...

509
00:56:52,491 --> 00:56:57,326
...because I thought that way, you know,
you could put your own things up.

510
00:56:58,730 --> 00:57:02,723
-I like the Dürer watercolor.
-You know who Dürer is?

511
00:57:03,235 --> 00:57:07,194
-My mother's an artist.
-Oh, that's right. Of course.

512
00:57:07,372 --> 00:57:13,174
Of course. They said that. Hey, listen.
Do you want some tea or something?

513
00:57:13,345 --> 00:57:18,942
Or Pepsi. I bought Pepsi. I didn't know
what you'd drink. We have juice.

514
00:57:19,117 --> 00:57:23,417
